<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-05-12T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-05-12T02:00:00-05:00" n="1290" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1290">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">125.8573/5–1249: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-05-12T15:00:00+08:00">May 12,
                                    1949—3 p. m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received May 12—9:06 a. m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1611. Security officer recommends arming American guards with 45–caliber
                            pistols. Appreciate expression Department policy this matter.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Cabot</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>